1
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,040
=Love Again=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,110
=Episode 13=

3
00:01:39,220 --> 00:01:40,149
It's already time.

4
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:41,130
Should be here soon.

5
00:01:41,780 --> 00:01:42,389
There he comes.

6
00:01:42,390 --> 00:01:43,060
Look.

7
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:44,810
Speak of the man.

8
00:01:46,030 --> 00:01:47,499
- Zhang.
- Good morning, Mr. Shen.

9
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,280
- Good work.
- Were you waiting for your letter?

10
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:50,410
No, not really.

11
00:01:51,110 --> 00:01:52,850
Let's see
if there's a letter for you today.

12
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:54,250
Is there?

13
00:01:56,740 --> 00:01:58,029
Sorry. No, sir.

14
00:01:58,030 --> 00:01:59,010
All for the neighborhood.

15
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:00,219
All for the neighborhood.

16
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:00,940
All right.

17
00:02:01,310 --> 00:02:03,180
Just leave them inside the guardhouse.

18
00:02:03,340 --> 00:02:03,709
Thanks.

19
00:02:03,710 --> 00:02:04,660
Someone will handle them.

20
00:02:05,990 --> 00:02:07,060
Ms. Baoqin!

21
00:02:08,340 --> 00:02:10,059
Here to cook for Lina again?

22
00:02:10,060 --> 00:02:11,029
Yes.

23
00:02:11,030 --> 00:02:11,709
Take care.

24
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:12,869
- I will.
- I'm heading back.

25
00:02:12,870 --> 00:02:14,500
All right. Goodbye.

26
00:02:14,830 --> 00:02:15,500
All right.

27
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:21,220
Good morning, ma'am!

28
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:23,850
Good morning!

29
00:02:23,940 --> 00:02:24,659
I saw

30
00:02:24,660 --> 00:02:26,219
a small goods store having a sale

31
00:02:26,220 --> 00:02:26,779
over there!

32
00:02:26,780 --> 00:02:27,200
A sale?

33
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,979
They were announcing it
on a loudspeaker! Hurry!

34
00:02:28,979 --> 00:02:30,059
Really? Chat another time!

35
00:02:30,060 --> 00:02:31,109
I have to check it out!

36
00:02:31,110 --> 00:02:31,939
Take it easy, ma'am!

37
00:02:31,940 --> 00:02:33,090
Will do!

38
00:02:37,220 --> 00:02:39,130
How long is your mother
going to stay here?

39
00:02:40,310 --> 00:02:41,500
What's that supposed to mean?

40
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:42,989
She wouldn't sleep last night.

41
00:02:42,990 --> 00:02:44,220
Kept watching me work.

42
00:02:44,310 --> 00:02:45,740
She even asked about my dad.

43
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:47,690
She wanted to set him up with someone.

44
00:02:47,710 --> 00:02:48,339
I think

45
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:49,380
the name was Peng-something.

46
00:02:50,390 --> 00:02:51,629
Give me a break.

47
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:52,659
Peng Yulan.

48
00:02:52,660 --> 00:02:54,250
She's my mom's ex-colleague.

49
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:57,210
She's just concerned about your dad.

50
00:02:57,630 --> 00:02:59,860
Well, I thank your mother
for her concern on his behalf.

51
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,650
Can we ask her to stop worrying so much?

52
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:03,210
I couldn't even

53
00:03:03,660 --> 00:03:05,100
finish the financial statement.

54
00:03:06,030 --> 00:03:07,380
How can you blame my mother

55
00:03:07,590 --> 00:03:08,650
for that?

56
00:03:09,220 --> 00:03:10,890
Are you going to blame her

57
00:03:11,220 --> 00:03:13,330
if you can't get
your company listed too?

58
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:17,069
She came to look after
her injured daughter.

59
00:03:17,070 --> 00:03:18,219
Can't you give her some grace?

60
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:19,770
Be a better son-in-law.

61
00:03:20,630 --> 00:03:23,380
I've been taking care
of this household for over 20 years.

62
00:03:23,420 --> 00:03:25,010
Have I ever complained?

63
00:03:25,150 --> 00:03:26,589
Well, you're complaining right now,

64
00:03:26,590 --> 00:03:27,779
aren't you?

65
00:03:27,780 --> 00:03:29,570
I do the chores. Do you?

66
00:03:30,190 --> 00:03:32,899
If you don't manage the house,
you don't get to complain.

67
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:35,620
You're eating my mom's cooking.
Show some respect.

68
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:37,130
Where's your gratitude?

69
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:39,620
I have it right here. I'm grateful.

70
00:03:39,710 --> 00:03:42,219
She can stay for as long as she wants.

71
00:03:42,220 --> 00:03:43,300
She can stay for 20 years.

72
00:03:46,340 --> 00:03:48,200
You think I like
having her here all the time?

73
00:03:48,460 --> 00:03:50,099
I wouldn't need her here

74
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:51,770
if you were more reliable.

75
00:03:52,830 --> 00:03:53,859
Go cut up an orange.

76
00:03:53,860 --> 00:03:55,100
Duole likes oranges.

77
00:03:55,460 --> 00:03:56,540
For Duole?

78
00:04:00,460 --> 00:04:01,330
Mom.

79
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:03,010
Where are my football socks?

80
00:04:03,030 --> 00:04:04,420
I put them in the shoebox for you.

81
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,130
We're having egg pancakes?

82
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:10,540
Granny's the best.

83
00:04:10,980 --> 00:04:13,740
Your granny got up early
and started busying herself.

84
00:04:14,510 --> 00:04:16,500
She went out to buy groceries.

85
00:04:16,710 --> 00:04:18,420
Guess all that flattery was for nothing.

86
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:22,189
Here, Duole, have an orange.

87
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:23,600
What else do you need me to do?

88
00:04:24,780 --> 00:04:25,629
Here, Mom.

89
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:26,570
Have a slice of orange.

90
00:04:29,390 --> 00:04:30,380
See?

91
00:04:30,590 --> 00:04:31,650
Only my son and my mom

92
00:04:31,660 --> 00:04:33,690
spoil me in this house.

93
00:04:36,270 --> 00:04:37,100
Have some milk.

94
00:04:37,390 --> 00:04:37,980
Here.

95
00:04:38,150 --> 00:04:39,269
He's almost as tall as I am.

96
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:41,010
He can pour his own milk.

97
00:04:41,660 --> 00:04:43,219
Even if he grows
as tall as a utility pole,

98
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:44,339
he's still my son.

99
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:44,949
Right, Duole?

100
00:04:44,950 --> 00:04:45,740
That's right.

101
00:04:48,780 --> 00:04:49,829
My hand's still healing.

102
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:52,010
I asked you to help blow-dry my hair,
and you wouldn't.

103
00:04:52,420 --> 00:04:53,749
But look at your dad.

104
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:56,770
He was massaging Ms. Lian's shoulders
and even blow-drying her hair.

105
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:59,300
You're not even as considerate
as a 70-year-old man.

106
00:04:59,710 --> 00:05:02,330
Well, Ms. Lian also gave Dad
foot baths and massages.

107
00:05:02,540 --> 00:05:04,130
Well, I gave you a son!

108
00:05:05,190 --> 00:05:06,300
What's so funny?

109
00:05:10,540 --> 00:05:12,180
Everybody's up and having breakfast.

110
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:12,539
Mom.

111
00:05:12,540 --> 00:05:13,760
Don't get up.

112
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:15,659
- Don't worry about me.
- Let me help you.

113
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:17,099
- Just leave them there.
- All right.

114
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:18,060
I'll be right over.

115
00:05:18,420 --> 00:05:19,540
I bought

116
00:05:19,710 --> 00:05:21,450
a ton of things today.

117
00:05:21,860 --> 00:05:23,940
Spare ribs, oxtail.

118
00:05:24,070 --> 00:05:26,300
All of Duole's favorites.

119
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:28,380
Le.

120
00:05:28,830 --> 00:05:30,339
Isn't it great that I'm here?

121
00:05:30,340 --> 00:05:31,450
Yes!

122
00:05:31,510 --> 00:05:33,130
Granny,
you should just live here with us.

123
00:05:33,780 --> 00:05:35,180
All right. I'll stay.

124
00:05:36,190 --> 00:05:37,690
She's serious.

125
00:05:42,030 --> 00:05:42,940
Duole,

126
00:05:43,390 --> 00:05:45,810
your hair is growing back.

127
00:05:46,030 --> 00:05:48,860
Tonight, I'll take you to get a trim.

128
00:05:51,030 --> 00:05:52,219
Yes. The weather's getting hot.

129
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:53,810
Might as well shave it all off.

130
00:05:53,950 --> 00:05:54,860
Save some money.

131
00:05:56,660 --> 00:05:58,440
I'm going to be late for school.
I have to go.

132
00:05:58,510 --> 00:05:58,899
Take care.

133
00:05:58,900 --> 00:05:59,879
- Take care.
- Easy there.

134
00:05:59,879 --> 00:06:01,589
- Did you finish your breakfast?
- Yes.

135
00:06:01,590 --> 00:06:02,690
All right. Be careful.

136
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:03,829
Bye, Granny!

137
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:05,300
Goodbye.

138
00:06:05,590 --> 00:06:08,450
Slow down.
Put your shoes on properly first.

139
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:12,859
Take it easy, Duole. Slow down.

140
00:06:12,860 --> 00:06:13,570
Right.

141
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:16,570
Shen Qing.

142
00:06:16,830 --> 00:06:18,690
Do take to heart

143
00:06:18,780 --> 00:06:20,890
what I told you last night.

144
00:06:23,030 --> 00:06:24,219
You're your father's son.

145
00:06:24,220 --> 00:06:25,330
You have to help your dad

146
00:06:25,460 --> 00:06:26,770
steer his ship properly.

147
00:06:27,630 --> 00:06:28,450
Got it.

148
00:06:30,070 --> 00:06:32,250
I need to send an email.

149
00:06:32,510 --> 00:06:34,540
- Have breakfast, Mom.
- Oh, all right.

150
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,269
Mom,

151
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:39,860
what did you tell Shen Qing last night?

152
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:40,299
I...

153
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,189
You can be

154
00:06:41,190 --> 00:06:43,330
quite tactless when you speak.

155
00:06:43,540 --> 00:06:45,029
Vixens spout all the honeyed words.

156
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:47,029
Honest folk like us...

157
00:06:47,030 --> 00:06:47,979
Shush.

158
00:06:47,980 --> 00:06:49,979
We tell it like it is.

159
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:51,250
Stop talking.

160
00:06:54,460 --> 00:06:55,810
Zhuoran!

161
00:06:58,710 --> 00:07:00,300
I'm coming in!

162
00:07:34,870 --> 00:07:36,010
Baoqin.

163
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:38,930
Peng Yulan.

164
00:07:40,110 --> 00:07:42,340
I'm at your old prince charming's place.

165
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:43,269
Listen.

166
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:44,179
He collects stamps too.

167
00:07:44,180 --> 00:07:45,010
Check it out.

168
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:52,410
Such a cultured man.

169
00:07:52,820 --> 00:07:54,380
Of course.

170
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:56,269
Who do you think Zhuoran is?

171
00:07:56,270 --> 00:07:58,050
He's a university professor.

172
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:03,349
Listen to me, Peng Yulan.

173
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:05,469
A house is not a home without a woman.

174
00:08:05,470 --> 00:08:06,580
Look at this place.

175
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:08,220
Dirty, dirty, dirty.

176
00:08:08,510 --> 00:08:10,130
All right. I won't keep you any longer.

177
00:08:10,150 --> 00:08:11,650
I have to mop the floor.

178
00:08:12,110 --> 00:08:14,380
Baoqin, you have a lot on your hands.

179
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:16,460
You have to help out with a lot.

180
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:19,770
Peng Yulan, you just reminded me.

181
00:08:19,940 --> 00:08:20,740
Here's what we'll do.

182
00:08:20,940 --> 00:08:22,410
Stay on standby.

183
00:08:23,060 --> 00:08:24,620
Be ready anytime I call.

184
00:08:52,390 --> 00:08:52,899
You're home.

185
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:53,700
Baoqin...

186
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:54,820
It's you.

187
00:08:55,180 --> 00:08:56,130
Morning.

188
00:08:56,350 --> 00:08:57,500
It's not morning anymore.

189
00:08:59,230 --> 00:09:00,389
I bought you some fresh liver.

190
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:01,700
It's in the fridge.

191
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:02,899
Oh, thank you.

192
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:05,299
Your floor was filthy,
so I figured I'd wipe it for you.

193
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:07,220
Put your feet up and change
into your slippers.

194
00:09:07,870 --> 00:09:08,980
Don't move

195
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:09,819
while

196
00:09:09,820 --> 00:09:11,170
I mop the floor.

197
00:09:11,990 --> 00:09:14,469
You can move after the floor dries.

198
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:15,059
All right?

199
00:09:15,060 --> 00:09:16,250
Feet up, please.

200
00:09:19,180 --> 00:09:19,629
Yes.

201
00:09:19,630 --> 00:09:20,749
That's good.

202
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:22,200
Let me wipe that spot for you.

203
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:26,100
I saw a fan on the desk.

204
00:09:26,180 --> 00:09:28,460
The painting on it is really well done.
Who painted it?

205
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:32,930
A friend of mine.

206
00:09:34,940 --> 00:09:36,100
I know who it is.

207
00:09:36,350 --> 00:09:37,380
You do?

208
00:09:38,940 --> 00:09:40,010
Du Liniang.

209
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:42,989
Feet up.

210
00:09:42,990 --> 00:09:44,170
Yes.

211
00:09:44,230 --> 00:09:45,620
That is Du Liniang.

212
00:09:46,030 --> 00:09:47,899
Judging by the delicate brushwork,

213
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:50,299
it's obviously done by a woman.

214
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:51,580
It's a woman, right?

215
00:09:52,420 --> 00:09:53,170
Yes.

216
00:09:53,990 --> 00:09:56,860
Feet up.

217
00:09:56,990 --> 00:09:58,899
I'll be done in no time.

218
00:09:58,900 --> 00:09:59,469
Here.

219
00:09:59,470 --> 00:10:01,629
Take your shoes off.
Let me see if the soles are dirty.

220
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:03,539
- Let me clean them for you.
- It's all right...

221
00:10:03,540 --> 00:10:03,989
Zhuoran.

222
00:10:03,990 --> 00:10:05,290
This is fine.

223
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:07,299
Wait, Zhuoran...

224
00:10:07,300 --> 00:10:08,539
- Your shoes...
- You carry on.

225
00:10:08,540 --> 00:10:10,100
I'm not done yet.

226
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:12,250
Lina.

227
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:14,939
Dad.

228
00:10:14,940 --> 00:10:15,700
Lina.

229
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:17,419
Your mom came to my place

230
00:10:17,420 --> 00:10:19,250
early in the morning to clean the floor.

231
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:21,220
And she rummaged through everything...

232
00:10:21,270 --> 00:10:22,749
You need to talk to her.

233
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:24,220
This is inappropriate.

234
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:26,179
My mom just has to stay busy.

235
00:10:26,180 --> 00:10:26,629
You see...

236
00:10:26,630 --> 00:10:28,629
My hand got burned, Dad.

237
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:31,290
My mom came over
to help me out with some chores.

238
00:10:31,510 --> 00:10:32,860
You burned your hand?

239
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:35,579
And pretty badly, too.

240
00:10:35,580 --> 00:10:36,469
When did that happen?

241
00:10:36,470 --> 00:10:37,860
Where did you get burned?

242
00:10:38,660 --> 00:10:40,410
At your place.

243
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:42,170
At my place?

244
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:44,050
I wasn't aware of this.

245
00:10:44,470 --> 00:10:46,349
Do you need to go to the hospital?

246
00:10:46,350 --> 00:10:47,290
It looks bad.

247
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:50,469
Did you put anything on it for the burn?
You can't just leave it like that.

248
00:10:50,470 --> 00:10:51,939
I'm fine. Don't worry about it, Dad.

249
00:10:51,940 --> 00:10:54,770
Go back and enjoy your opera. I'm fine.

250
00:10:54,780 --> 00:10:55,700
But I...

251
00:10:56,110 --> 00:10:57,109
Forget about the opera.

252
00:10:57,110 --> 00:10:59,980
Your mother's louder than any opera.

253
00:11:00,110 --> 00:11:01,460
She scares me.

254
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:05,659
My mom's not a tiger.
Why are you guys so afraid of her?

255
00:11:05,660 --> 00:11:08,050
It's not about that.

256
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:08,740
She...

257
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:10,650
Never mind...

258
00:11:13,350 --> 00:11:15,410
Almost forgot what I came for.

259
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:18,029
Your mother made me keep my feet up
the entire time she mopped.

260
00:11:18,030 --> 00:11:20,340
She said my shoes' soles are dirty.

261
00:11:20,350 --> 00:11:22,059
Do you have a cloth
or something I can use?

262
00:11:22,060 --> 00:11:23,860
Oh, yes. I'll get it for you.

263
00:11:25,230 --> 00:11:26,410
My phone's ringing!

264
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:37,100
Don't run!

265
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,539
Don't run! The floor's slippery!

266
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:40,269
- I...
- The old man that lives across from us

267
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:42,130
- had a fall and was paralyzed!
- Hello?

268
00:11:48,390 --> 00:11:49,290
Please leave.

269
00:11:56,230 --> 00:11:56,890
Hello?

270
00:11:58,110 --> 00:11:59,010
Ms. Nie?

271
00:11:59,420 --> 00:12:01,130
I got your postcard.

272
00:12:01,580 --> 00:12:02,500
I lost

273
00:12:02,780 --> 00:12:03,860
the game.

274
00:12:05,350 --> 00:12:07,530
I went to the gatehouse
early this morning.

275
00:12:08,230 --> 00:12:09,349
There wasn't any mail for me,

276
00:12:09,350 --> 00:12:11,740
so I knew you must've lost.

277
00:12:16,660 --> 00:12:17,650
Did you read it?

278
00:12:18,870 --> 00:12:21,460
"Days were slower in the past.

279
00:12:21,940 --> 00:12:24,620
Carriage, horse, and mail

280
00:12:24,621 --> 00:12:25,620
did not reach fast.

281
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:27,500
You needed a lifetime

