Folk Kunqu carries

562
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:21,580
its own unique charm.

563
00:24:23,060 --> 00:24:24,060
Would you like to hear it?

564
00:24:28,670 --> 00:24:30,170
I knew it.

565
00:24:31,230 --> 00:24:32,730
I recorded it for you.

566
00:24:33,510 --> 00:24:34,299
Give me a second.

567
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:35,540
I'll play it for you.

568
00:25:57,190 --> 00:25:58,210
You're back.

569
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:01,340
I'm back.

570
00:26:04,140 --> 00:26:05,410
Listen to this.

571
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:07,580
Your father-in-law.

572
00:26:08,750 --> 00:26:11,020
Your father-in-law is out of his mind!

573
00:26:11,540 --> 00:26:13,060
He ran out into the rain

574
00:26:14,540 --> 00:26:16,580
just to record some opera!

575
00:26:16,820 --> 00:26:17,749
Record?

576
00:26:17,750 --> 00:26:18,890
Yes!

577
00:26:19,190 --> 00:26:21,170
Dragging mud with his every step.

578
00:26:22,140 --> 00:26:23,020
Where is he?

579
00:26:23,340 --> 00:26:24,059
He left.

580
00:26:24,060 --> 00:26:25,490
Ran off in a flash.

581
00:26:25,820 --> 00:26:27,930
As if the fairy fed him an elixir.

582
00:26:30,060 --> 00:26:31,269
He came back for his call.

583
00:26:31,270 --> 00:26:33,130
Every day at exactly 3 PM.

584
00:26:37,910 --> 00:26:39,580
I knew it...

585
00:26:39,750 --> 00:26:40,380
Mom.

586
00:26:40,510 --> 00:26:41,059
No wonder...

587
00:26:41,060 --> 00:26:42,060
Dry your hair.

588
00:26:42,470 --> 00:26:44,340
I was wondering why he ran off so fast.

589
00:26:44,510 --> 00:26:46,100
Like he'd been injected with adrenaline.

590
00:26:47,910 --> 00:26:49,859
Peng Yulan put in so much effort

591
00:26:49,860 --> 00:26:51,170
to prepare these pork knuckles,

592
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:54,730
but she still lost
to a phone call from that fairy.

593
00:26:56,140 --> 00:26:58,029
I just don't get men.

594
00:26:58,030 --> 00:26:58,709
Men

595
00:26:58,710 --> 00:27:00,690
are so easily obsessed.

596
00:27:01,030 --> 00:27:03,859
Mom, this is different.

597
00:27:03,860 --> 00:27:04,860
How?

598
00:27:05,580 --> 00:27:07,620
Either way,
obsessions make you lose your appetite.

599
00:27:08,380 --> 00:27:09,730
Even pork knuckles don't tempt him.

600
00:27:11,270 --> 00:27:12,779
I think this is a good thing.

601
00:27:12,780 --> 00:27:13,859
Look at my father-in-law.

602
00:27:13,860 --> 00:27:16,060
Now he's listening to opera,
writing letters...

603
00:27:16,270 --> 00:27:17,730
He's young again.

604
00:27:18,100 --> 00:27:19,450
Full of energy.

605
00:27:19,670 --> 00:27:21,130
"Full of energy"?

606
00:27:21,190 --> 00:27:22,509
That's not energy.

607
00:27:22,510 --> 00:27:23,780
That's being possessed.

608
00:27:25,950 --> 00:27:27,260
Peng Yulan...

609
00:27:27,580 --> 00:27:29,139
Peng Yulan will be heartbroken again.

610
00:27:29,140 --> 00:27:29,860
I mean,

611
00:27:30,470 --> 00:27:32,509
she managed to outlast Ms. Lian,

612
00:27:32,510 --> 00:27:33,860
and now another fairy has appeared.

613
00:27:34,230 --> 00:27:35,860
She had her hopes up, too.

614
00:27:36,100 --> 00:27:38,229
I don't even know
how to break it to her.

615
00:27:38,230 --> 00:27:39,380
With things like this,

616
00:27:39,990 --> 00:27:40,989
the sooner you tell her,

617
00:27:40,990 --> 00:27:42,130
the better.

618
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:45,100
You're right.

619
00:27:45,990 --> 00:27:47,139
Hesitation only

620
00:27:47,140 --> 00:27:48,490
makes things worse.

621
00:27:49,300 --> 00:27:49,970
All right.

622
00:27:50,140 --> 00:27:51,410
I'll make a trip home.

623
00:27:51,620 --> 00:27:52,669
Don't bother coming back.

624
00:27:52,670 --> 00:27:54,170
My hand is almost healed anyway.

625
00:27:54,670 --> 00:27:55,509
What?

626
00:27:55,510 --> 00:27:56,620
Are you kicking me out?

627
00:27:57,340 --> 00:28:00,539
I've been staying here every day,
doing chores and cooking for you.

628
00:28:00,540 --> 00:28:01,619
You've had it easy.

629
00:28:01,620 --> 00:28:03,410
Don't you enjoy having me here?

630
00:28:06,030 --> 00:28:07,450
But what about Dad?

631
00:28:07,750 --> 00:28:09,130
He doesn't know how to cook.

632
00:28:10,100 --> 00:28:12,269
- He's just making do every day.
- He's fine...

633
00:28:12,270 --> 00:28:15,100
Older men are in high demand these days.

634
00:28:15,510 --> 00:28:16,650
My dad has a good temper.

635
00:28:21,380 --> 00:28:22,020
Well...

636
00:28:22,540 --> 00:28:23,620
I'll head back then.

637
00:28:26,780 --> 00:28:28,540
It's raining outside. Be careful.

638
00:28:28,780 --> 00:28:29,690
Got it.

639
00:28:33,582 --> 00:28:35,509
(Chief Operating Officer)

640
00:28:35,510 --> 00:28:37,260
The patent we acquired

641
00:28:38,140 --> 00:28:40,890
can improve the stability
of the M701 targeted drug.

642
00:28:41,270 --> 00:28:43,890
It's also crucial
for the development of M703.

643
00:28:44,030 --> 00:28:45,949
Why can't we launch both together?

644
00:28:45,950 --> 00:28:47,580
Dr. Qin said we can.

645
00:28:47,780 --> 00:28:49,539
Dr. Qin is only responsible for R&D.

646
00:28:49,540 --> 00:28:51,379
He doesn't handle
the market side of things.

647
00:28:51,380 --> 00:28:54,339
Right now,
M701 is in a critical trial phase.

648
00:28:54,340 --> 00:28:57,029
For a blockbuster drug like this,
any delay in launch means

649
00:28:57,030 --> 00:28:59,509
competitors will take market share.

650
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:01,509
The potential losses
to the company are immeasurable.

651
00:29:01,510 --> 00:29:04,039
But M703 is a blockbuster drug too.

652
00:29:04,039 --> 00:29:06,080
We have the capability
to develop both simultaneously.

653
00:29:06,080 --> 00:29:07,229
We don't.

654
00:29:07,230 --> 00:29:08,300
We're not short on money.

655
00:29:08,860 --> 00:29:11,060
- We're short on human resources.
- Then hire!

656
00:29:11,140 --> 00:29:12,139
Have HR search worldwide!

657
00:29:12,140 --> 00:29:13,690
Spare no expense.

658
00:29:14,100 --> 00:29:16,580
That still takes time.

659
00:29:18,470 --> 00:29:20,779
How about this?

660
00:29:20,780 --> 00:29:21,650
Ask Ice.

661
00:29:22,190 --> 00:29:23,410
See if the investors

662
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:26,890
are willing to give M703 more time.

663
00:29:30,540 --> 00:29:31,340
Qing.

664
00:29:31,950 --> 00:29:33,509
Why are you silent?

665
00:29:33,510 --> 00:29:34,859
Can you ask her now?

666
00:29:34,860 --> 00:29:36,620
Right now, at this very moment.

667
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:37,539
Hurry!

668
00:29:37,540 --> 00:29:38,820
Time waits for no one!

669
00:29:39,540 --> 00:29:40,210
Please?

670
00:29:50,620 --> 00:29:51,340
Over here.

671
00:29:53,230 --> 00:29:53,970
I'm here.

672
00:29:54,990 --> 00:29:55,930
It's windy.

673
00:29:57,510 --> 00:29:58,690
Did I pull you away from work?

674
00:29:59,950 --> 00:30:02,580
It's fine. I was just about
to come down for a cup of coffee.

675
00:30:06,270 --> 00:30:07,299
About the M703

676
00:30:07,300 --> 00:30:09,450
you mentioned on the phone,

677
00:30:09,820 --> 00:30:11,060
my suggestion is for you

678
00:30:11,910 --> 00:30:13,490
to put together a report first.

679
00:30:13,540 --> 00:30:16,210
Explain the drug's
pharmacology and efficacy,

680
00:30:16,300 --> 00:30:17,669
and why it should be developed

681
00:30:17,670 --> 00:30:18,780
alongside M701.

682
00:30:19,300 --> 00:30:20,260
Also,

683
00:30:20,380 --> 00:30:22,619
break the development
into different stages,

684
00:30:22,620 --> 00:30:24,709
detailing the time and budget for each.

685
00:30:24,710 --> 00:30:26,650
So we'll have a basis for judgment,

686
00:30:26,950 --> 00:30:29,490
and our fund can make a quick decision.

687
00:30:30,670 --> 00:30:32,650
That's great!
I'll prepare it as soon as I return.

688
00:30:39,540 --> 00:30:41,500
(Li Ya)

689
00:30:42,060 --> 00:30:44,170
You can take that.
I'll go put in our orders.

690
00:30:44,340 --> 00:30:45,490
It's fine.

691
00:30:45,620 --> 00:30:46,490
It's my ex.

692
00:30:52,620 --> 00:30:54,130
Nice ringtone.

693
00:30:55,030 --> 00:30:55,860
Really?

694
00:30:56,580 --> 00:30:58,020
I composed it myself.

695
00:30:58,030 --> 00:30:59,170
I can send it to you.

696
00:30:59,270 --> 00:31:00,780
You compose music too?

697
00:31:01,710 --> 00:31:02,780
Just for fun.

698
00:31:44,300 --> 00:31:48,450
♪The night flows like a gentle stream♪

699
00:31:50,300 --> 00:31:53,730
♪But I am not there to share its gleam♪

700
00:31:57,948 --> 00:32:00,890
(Write of how you gaze at the moon above.
Let the nightingale sing in my place.)

701
00:32:01,510 --> 00:32:05,690
♪The night flows like a gentle stream♪

702
00:32:07,540 --> 00:32:10,860
♪But I am not there to share its gleam♪

703
00:32:11,340 --> 00:32:15,540
♪So borrow a poem from the night for me♪

704
00:32:17,230 --> 00:32:23,060
♪Let its first line
lift the blinds of your soul♪

705
00:32:23,860 --> 00:32:29,210
♪Write of how you gaze at the moon above♪

706
00:32:31,990 --> 00:32:38,890
♪Let the nightingale sing in my place♪

707
00:32:39,540 --> 00:32:46,820
♪Write of the boundless night
outside your pane♪

708
00:32:55,892 --> 00:32:59,362
♪But I am not there to share its gleam...♪

709
00:33:01,660 --> 00:33:02,860
Why'd you stop?

710
00:33:03,740 --> 00:33:04,860
It sounds nice.

711
00:33:05,180 --> 00:33:06,380
What song is that?

712
00:33:07,180 --> 00:33:08,260
Just something I hummed.

713
00:33:08,830 --> 00:33:11,349
Qing! Check out
this trendy shoe polish I bought!

714
00:33:11,350 --> 00:33:13,340
It makes old shoes look brand new.

715
00:33:20,180 --> 00:33:21,259
Stop.

716
00:33:21,260 --> 00:33:22,949
Your hand isn't fully healed yet.

717
00:33:22,950 --> 00:33:23,789
It's fine now.

718
00:33:23,790 --> 00:33:24,349
Stop fussing.

719
00:33:24,350 --> 00:33:25,450
Come on, stop.

720
00:33:28,220 --> 00:33:29,780
How is this fussing?

721
00:33:30,140 --> 00:33:31,739
Your dress shoes are all dirty.

722
00:33:31,740 --> 00:33:33,539
People will say your wife is lazy.

723
00:33:33,540 --> 00:33:34,890
Let them say whatever they want.

724
00:33:35,030 --> 00:33:36,970
No one gets to talk about my wife.

725
00:33:37,030 --> 00:33:38,010
No more polishing.

726
00:33:43,030 --> 00:33:44,490
It really works.

727
00:33:44,830 --> 00:33:45,610
Lina.

728
00:33:47,100 --> 00:33:50,340
I'm in the mood for some watermelon.
Let's go buy one together.

729
00:33:50,580 --> 00:33:51,869
Aren't you going for a run today?

730
00:33:51,870 --> 00:33:52,660
Not today.

731
00:33:54,580 --> 00:33:56,829
Always come in hot but never last long.

732
00:33:56,830 --> 00:33:57,820
I'll get changed.

733
00:33:58,060 --> 00:33:58,890
Wait for me.

734
00:34:01,060 --> 00:34:02,010
Shen Qing.

735
00:34:02,660 --> 00:34:04,610
If I leave this world first,

736
00:34:04,790 --> 00:34:06,909
find another who will shine
your shoes for you.

737
00:34:06,910 --> 00:34:08,619
Don't find someone like the fairy.

738
00:34:08,620 --> 00:34:10,619
You'll outlive me.

739
00:34:10,620 --> 00:34:12,300
You have the longevity gene
in your family.

740
00:34:13,310 --> 00:34:14,860
And if you go first?

741
00:34:15,470 --> 00:34:17,450
Then you find someone
who will dry your hair for you.

742
00:34:17,740 --> 00:34:19,349
I won't bother looking.

743
00:34:19,350 --> 00:34:21,610
Took so long to finally get rid of you.

744
00:34:22,180 --> 00:34:25,389
After a lifetime of work,

745
00:34:25,390 --> 00:34:28,220
I should get to rest.

746
00:34:28,310 --> 00:34:31,180
You've never been in tune
even when we were in university. Stop singing.

747
00:34:32,470 --> 00:34:33,700
Let's hurry home.

748
00:34:36,790 --> 00:34:37,780
What is it?

749
00:34:39,580 --> 00:34:40,780
Listen...

750
00:34:44,140 --> 00:34:46,380
Professor Shen is in love again?

751
00:34:48,660 --> 00:34:50,050
Looks like it.

752
00:34:50,140 --> 00:34:51,530
I can't say for sure.

753
00:34:52,030 --> 00:34:55,930
But they only write and call each other.

754
00:34:57,510 --> 00:34:58,930
What's with that?

755
00:34:59,540 --> 00:35:01,140
I don't know either.

756
00:35:04,740 --> 00:35:05,820
Peng Yulan, you...

757
00:35:06,660 --> 00:35:08,970
You should heed my advice.

758
00:35:09,660 --> 00:35:11,869
Maybe you should just

759
00:35:11,870 --> 00:35:12,890
let things go

760
00:35:13,470 --> 00:35:14,450
with Zhuoran.

761
00:35:14,580 --> 00:35:16,450
He didn't even take a single bite

762
00:35:17,350 --> 00:35:18,380
of your pork knuckles.

763
00:35:24,430 --> 00:35:26,059
There are plenty of fish in the sea.

764
00:35:26,060 --> 00:35:27,949
I think you'd be better off

765
00:35:27,950 --> 00:35:30,179
finding someone a little younger

766
00:35:30,180 --> 00:35:31,450
than Zhuoran.

767
00:35:32,030 --> 00:35:34,530
Someone to dance with you

768
00:35:35,180 --> 00:35:36,180
and all that.

769
00:35:41,620 --> 00:35:42,570
Peng Yulan.

770
00:35:44,060 --> 00:35:44,820
Peng Yulan?

771
00:35:45,740 --> 00:35:46,820
Baoqin.

772
00:35:47,540 --> 00:35:48,820
I'm stubborn.

773
00:35:49,510 --> 00:35:51,220
I like Professor Shen.

774
00:35:51,580 --> 00:35:53,259
If she's enchanting his soul,

775
00:35:53,260 --> 00:35:54,380
then I'll enchant his stomach.

776
00:35:54,790 --> 00:35:56,490
It's a fair competition.

777
00:35:57,910 --> 00:35:59,450
Peng Yulan...

778
00:36:03,830 --> 00:36:04,989
I...

779
00:36:04,990 --> 00:36:06,389
I'm seeing you in a new light!

780
00:36:06,390 --> 00:36:08,570
You've got my respect.

781
00:36:08,660 --> 00:36:09,700
You've got it.

782
00:36:10,060 --> 00:36:11,300
If that's the case,

783
00:36:13,260 --> 00:36:14,860
then we can't be subtle anymore.

784
00:36:16,180 --> 00:36:17,610
When it's time to act,

785
00:36:17,790 --> 00:36:19,010
we act!

786
00:36:57,390 --> 00:36:58,740
This place is filthy.

787
00:36:58,910 --> 00:37:00,349
That aside,

788
00:37:00,350 --> 00:37:01,179
you...

789
00:37:01,180 --> 00:37:02,989
You're wasting your nightgown.

790
00:37:02,990 --> 00:37:05,139
You should unbutton a few more.
Don't be shy.

791
00:37:05,140 --> 00:37:06,699
You need to show more skin.

792
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:08,619
- It's fine...
- Show some more skin. More!

793
00:37:08,620 --> 00:37:10,869
This is fine... Enough...

794
00:37:10,870 --> 00:37:12,340
Please!

795
00:37:12,430 --> 00:37:13,909
Stop teasing me!

796
00:37:13,910 --> 00:37:15,340
Act natural.

797
00:37:17,390 --> 00:37:18,340
Zhuoran.

798
00:37:18,390 --> 00:37:19,340
Look who's here!

799
00:37:20,510 --> 00:37:21,450
Peng.

800
00:37:22,990 --> 00:37:24,029
Professor Shen.

801
00:37:24,030 --> 00:37:24,930
Hello.

802
00:37:25,100 --> 00:37:26,010
Nice to see you.

803
00:37:26,060 --> 00:37:27,140
How can you let a guest...

804
00:37:27,620 --> 00:37:28,989
Here's the thing.

805
00:37:28,990 --> 00:37:30,469
I bought a big fish head today

806
00:37:30,470 --> 00:37:32,139
and I wanted to make it for lunch.

807
00:37:32,140 --> 00:37:33,389
But I don't know

808
00:37:33,390 --> 00:37:34,579
how to prepare it,

809
00:37:34,580 --> 00:37:36,219
so I invited Peng Yulan over.

810
00:37:36,220 --> 00:37:38,349
She's such a diligent homemaker.

811
00:37:38,350 --> 00:37:39,219
A virtuous woman.

812
00:37:39,220 --> 00:37:41,700
The moment she saw the floor,
she just started cleaning it.

813
00:37:42,180 --> 00:37:43,139
Thank you.

814
00:37:43,140 --> 00:37:44,099
Please sit down.

815
00:37:44,100 --> 00:37:45,179
It's all right.

816
00:37:45,180 --> 00:37:46,660
I like being busy.

817
00:37:46,990 --> 00:37:48,090
She's so diligent.

818
00:37:49,540 --> 00:37:51,660
Look how clean it is now.

819
00:37:52,310 --> 00:37:53,389
My shoes are dirty.

820
00:37:53,390 --> 00:37:56,440
I better not step in. I'll read the newspaper
while I wait in the other house.

821
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,530
Wait! Zhuoran!

822
00:37:59,140 --> 00:38:01,179
You don't have to do that.

823
00:38:01,180 --> 00:38:03,890
Peng Yulan cleaned all the soles too.

824
00:38:03,910 --> 00:38:05,700
Yes, all of them.

825
00:38:06,310 --> 00:38:07,699
Step however you want.

826
00:38:07,700 --> 00:38:09,309
- Come in.
- All right.

827
00:38:09,310 --> 00:38:11,259
Please have a seat, Professor.

828
00:38:11,260 --> 00:38:12,139
Please don't.

829
00:38:12,140 --> 00:38:13,209
I live here.

830
00:38:13,209 --> 00:38:15,129
- Let me pour you some water.
- Don't mind me.

831
00:38:15,129 --> 00:38:17,180
- Let me get you some water.
- Don't have to do that.

832
00:38:19,910 --> 00:38:20,869
I'll get that.

833
00:38:20,870 --> 00:38:21,530
I...

834
00:38:23,540 --> 00:38:24,860
Professor Shen! Are you...

835
00:38:25,620 --> 00:38:26,450
Hello?

836
00:38:27,430 --> 00:38:28,740
Gas company?

837
00:38:29,510 --> 00:38:31,389
- Wrong number!
- Are you all right?

838
00:38:31,390 --> 00:38:32,389
This isn't a gas company.

839
00:38:32,390 --> 00:38:33,869
- Are you all right?
- Sit down!

840
00:38:33,870 --> 00:38:34,659
Easy, easy.

841
00:38:34,660 --> 00:38:35,909
Zhuoran, slowly now.

842
00:38:35,910 --> 00:38:36,700
Easy there.

843
00:38:37,790 --> 00:38:39,220
Check his leg.

844
00:38:39,390 --> 00:38:40,219
How is it?

845
00:38:40,220 --> 00:38:41,300
Let's see it.

846
00:38:44,310 --> 00:38:44,949
It's swollen!

847
00:38:44,950 --> 00:38:46,570
There's bruising!

848
00:38:47,100 --> 00:38:48,949
I told you to slow down.

849
00:38:48,950 --> 00:38:50,949
What's the rush?

850
00:38:50,950 --> 00:38:52,029
You're too old for this.

851
00:38:52,030 --> 00:38:53,610
You need to ice this.

852
00:38:53,950 --> 00:38:55,010
Do you have any ice?

853
00:38:55,180 --> 00:38:55,789
In the freezer.

854
00:38:55,790 --> 00:38:57,490
- It's in the fridge.
- Let's go.

855
00:38:58,350 --> 00:38:59,410
Quickly!

856
00:39:00,790 --> 00:39:01,530
Here.

857
00:39:02,310 --> 00:39:03,220
Got the ice.

858
00:39:03,260 --> 00:39:04,140
Here's the ice.

859
00:39:04,740 --> 00:39:05,570
Let me see that.

860
00:39:06,540 --> 00:39:08,259
How's that? Too cold?

861
00:39:08,260 --> 00:39:09,469
Wrap it in a towel.

862
00:39:09,470 --> 00:39:10,820
Right, the towel.

863
00:39:11,740 --> 00:39:12,530
That's better.

864
00:39:12,830 --> 00:39:13,860
Thank you.

865
00:39:14,030 --> 00:39:14,829
Thank you, Peng.

866
00:39:14,830 --> 00:39:15,780
Better?

867
00:39:16,220 --> 00:39:17,530
Are we sure this is fine?

868
00:39:17,540 --> 00:39:18,139
Maybe he should

869
00:39:18,140 --> 00:39:19,820
get this checked at the hospital.

870
00:39:19,870 --> 00:39:21,179
Get an X-ray

871
00:39:21,180 --> 00:39:22,739
just in case.

872
00:39:22,740 --> 00:39:24,380
To be sure.

873
00:39:24,430 --> 00:39:26,570
You have money on your medical card.

874
00:39:26,660 --> 00:39:28,410
It's just a bump.

875
00:39:28,620 --> 00:39:29,789
I just need to ice it.

876
00:39:29,790 --> 00:39:31,309
Don't take this

877
00:39:31,310 --> 00:39:32,509
so lightly!

878
00:39:32,510 --> 00:39:34,699
The old man that lives across
from us fell the other day.

879
00:39:34,700 --> 00:39:37,440
He thought he was fine too.
He found himself paralyzed the next day.

880
00:39:39,580 --> 00:39:42,250
Getting to the hospital
could be a hassle too.

881
00:39:42,250 --> 00:39:44,309
Let's leave a cold compress on it
and see what happens.

882
00:39:44,310 --> 00:39:45,890
Right. Let's do that.

883
00:39:47,620 --> 00:39:48,970
Fine.

884
00:39:49,660 --> 00:39:52,509
You won't listen to me,
but you'll listen to Peng Yulan.

885
00:39:52,510 --> 00:39:53,450
Oh, you...

886
00:39:55,100 --> 00:39:56,260
Does it still hurt?

887
00:39:56,390 --> 00:39:57,579
No, I feel much better now.

888
00:39:57,580 --> 00:39:58,700
Thank you, Peng.

889
00:39:59,100 --> 00:39:59,989
Don't mention it.

890
00:39:59,990 --> 00:40:01,700
You seem experienced, Peng.

891
00:40:01,740 --> 00:40:03,539
Were you a doctor?

892
00:40:03,540 --> 00:40:04,780
No.

893
00:40:04,830 --> 00:40:07,300
I couldn't possibly be a doctor.

894
00:40:07,350 --> 00:40:08,989
My grandson does roller skating.

895
00:40:08,990 --> 00:40:10,789
He's always getting bumps and bruises.

896
00:40:10,790 --> 00:40:13,410
So I know learned how to handle this.

897
00:40:14,700 --> 00:40:16,179
For swelling,

898
00:40:16,180 --> 00:40:17,259
ice packs work best.

899
00:40:17,260 --> 00:40:18,140
You're right.

900
00:40:18,510 --> 00:40:19,570
Also helps with the pain.

901
00:40:19,790 --> 00:40:21,860
You learned through experience.

902
00:40:24,540 --> 00:40:25,610
How old is your grandson?

903
00:40:25,700 --> 00:40:26,820
He's in kindergarten.

904
00:40:27,950 --> 00:40:29,820
He's as mischievous as a little monkey.

905
00:40:30,740 --> 00:40:33,219
Duole was the same at that age.

906
00:40:33,220 --> 00:40:34,029
Is that so?

907
00:40:34,030 --> 00:40:36,340
Always climbing and jumping

908
00:40:36,470 --> 00:40:38,660
all over the place.

909
00:40:39,700 --> 00:40:41,469
Boys will be boys.

910
00:40:41,470 --> 00:40:44,259
Bring your grandson over sometime.

911
00:40:44,260 --> 00:40:45,099
Have Professor Shen

912
00:40:45,100 --> 00:40:46,429
teach him some calligraphy.

913
00:40:46,430 --> 00:40:47,890
Put a band-tightening spell on him.

914
00:40:49,870 --> 00:40:51,539
I can teach him calligraphy,

915
00:40:51,540 --> 00:40:53,260
but I can't put a golden hoop
around his head.

916
00:40:54,180 --> 00:40:56,010
I'm not the Jade Emperor.

917
00:40:57,430 --> 00:40:58,740
You're so funny.

918
00:40:58,870 --> 00:41:00,509
Leave him to me.

919
00:41:00,510 --> 00:41:01,490
Take it easy.

920
00:41:02,260 --> 00:41:03,380
You have a good chance.

921
00:41:07,220 --> 00:41:08,989
I don't recognize this character.

922
00:41:08,990 --> 00:41:10,660
How do you read this?

923
00:41:13,030 --> 00:41:13,860
Zhuoran.

924
00:41:13,950 --> 00:41:15,509
Made you some tea.

925
00:41:15,510 --> 00:41:16,570
I'll leave it here.

926
00:41:17,910 --> 00:41:18,890
Thank you.

927
00:41:19,030 --> 00:41:20,099
Oh, don't mention it.

928
00:41:20,100 --> 00:41:21,309
We're in-laws.

929
00:41:21,310 --> 00:41:22,909
Don't be so courteous.

930
00:41:22,910 --> 00:41:24,739
I just feel bad that I keep troubling you.

931
00:41:24,740 --> 00:41:25,820
It's not a problem.

932
00:41:25,830 --> 00:41:27,140
Listen.

933
00:41:27,180 --> 00:41:28,139
At our age,

934
00:41:28,140 --> 00:41:29,789
we need to slow down.

935
00:41:29,790 --> 00:41:31,450
You can't be hasty.

936
00:41:32,140 --> 00:41:32,909
All right.

937
00:41:32,910 --> 00:41:34,570
You should get some rest.

938
00:41:34,790 --> 00:41:36,050
I think I'll do a little reading.

939
00:41:36,060 --> 00:41:38,530
All right. I'll take my leave.

940
00:41:38,950 --> 00:41:40,349
Call me if you need anything.

941
00:41:40,350 --> 00:41:41,450
I know.

942
00:41:41,470 --> 00:41:42,660
All right.

943
00:41:50,060 --> 00:41:50,789
Is he asleep?

944
00:41:50,790 --> 00:41:52,260
No.

945
00:41:52,390 --> 00:41:56,659
Still reading. He's already old. It's not like
he's studying for college entrance exams.

946
00:41:56,660 --> 00:41:58,699
Doesn't he get tired of those books?

947
00:41:58,700 --> 00:41:59,820
You don't get it.

948
00:41:59,830 --> 00:42:01,309
Scholars

949
00:42:01,310 --> 00:42:02,700
are different.

950
00:42:03,350 --> 00:42:04,660
How is he different?

951
00:42:06,180 --> 00:42:06,539
Wait.

952
00:42:06,540 --> 00:42:07,970
Let me see what this is.

953
00:42:12,470 --> 00:42:13,740
Check this out.

954
00:42:14,350 --> 00:42:15,260
That fairy

955
00:42:16,140 --> 00:42:17,660
